topic.title: Ingress DPU Protection Information Request (IngressDpuProtectionReq)

body.p: Ingress DPU Protection Information Request message supports message length of 0.

table.title: Supported Ingress DPU PI Request Message Length

entry.p: * Message Length field in message header is Local Message Length plus one if it is for cascading, otherwise Message Length field is same as Local Message Length.

title.msg-desc: IngressDpuProtectionReq - Ingress DPU Protection Information Request Message

description.p: This field configures the ingress DPU request message type. Set this field to 1 to indicate the ingress DPU PI request message.

field-enum-def.field-enum-desc: Ingress DPU request message. Ingress DPU request message is used as both the message for encryption operation only or the message for full feature operation. Not valid for this message.
Ingress DPU PI request message. Ingress DPU PI request message is used as a message for PI1 and/or PI2 operation only.
Ingress DPU hash and compression request message. Ingress DPU hash and compression is used as a message for hash and/or compression operation only. Not valid for this message.
Invalid

description.p: This field configures the data flows that defines the sequences of data operations including functional bypass operations by processing engines. There are a total two valid data flow configurations with Type 1 Message Handler.

field-enum-def.field-enum-desc: The ingress DPU just moves the data stream from source to destination. All processing engines are bypassed
The ingress DPU performances PI operation by PI1 engine.

description.p: This field specifies the operation mode of PI1 engine.

field-enum-def.field-enum-desc: Check and forward PI field.
Check and strip PI field.
Insert PI field
Invalid

description.p: This field selects one of four protection information types.

field-enum-def.field-enum-desc: 16-bit Guard (CRC16), 16-bit Application Tag, 32-bit Reference Tag.
32-bit Guard (CRC32), 32-bit Reference Tag.
64-bit CRC only
Invalid

description.p: This bit enable/disable Guard field check or insertion.

field-enum-def.field-enum-desc: Disable Guard (CRC) checking in operation modes of PI1OpMode = 0 or 1; or disable Guard (CRC) insertion (insert zeros instead) in operation mode of PI1OpMode = 2.
Enable Guard (CRC) checking in operation modes of PI1OpMode = 0 or 1; or enable Guard (CRC) insertion in operation mode of PI1OpMode = 2.

description.p: This bit selects CRC (in Guard field) seed source either from PI1 PIDefaultCRCSeed register or from PI1CRCInitSeed field in this message.

field-enum-def.field-enum-desc: CRC seed source is from PI1 register PIDefaultSeed.
CRC seed source is from PI1CRCInitSeed field in this message.

description.p: This bit enables inversion in the output CRC generator.

field-enum-def.field-enum-desc: Normal CRC value is used for CRC checking operation modes of PI1OpMode = 0 or 1, or for CRC insertion in operation mode of PI1OpMode = 2.
CRC value is inverted and then used for CRC checking operation modes of PI1OpMode = 0 or 1, or for CRC insertion in operation mode of PI1OpMode = 2.

description.p: This bit enable/disable Application Tag field check or insertion.

field-enum-def.field-enum-desc: Disable Application Tag checking in operation modes of PI1OpMode = 0 or 1; or disable Application Tag insertion (insert zeros instead) in operation mode of PI1OpMode = 2.
Enable Application Tag checking in operation modes of PI1OpMode = 0 or 1; or enable Application Tag insertion in operation mode of PI1OpMode = 2.

description.p: This bit enable/disable Reference Tag field check or insertion.

field-enum-def.field-enum-desc: Disable Reference Tag checking in operation modes of PI1OpMode = 0 or 1; or disable Reference Tag insertion (insert zeros instead) in operation mode of PI1OpMode = 2.
Enable Reference Tag checking in operation modes of PI1OpMode = 0 or 1; or enable Reference Tag insertion in operation mode of PI1OpMode = 2.

description.p: This field specifies Reference Tag operation mode.

field-enum-def.field-enum-desc: Reference tag is incremental per logic block.
Reference tag is constant over all blocks
Always perform PI check per PI field processing configuration (PI1GuardEn, PI1AppTagEn, and PI1RefTagEn)
Disable PI check when Application Tag = "FFFF", regardless PI field processing configuration.
Disable PI check when Application Tag = "FFFF" and Reference Tag = "FFFF_FFFF" regardless PI field processing configuration.
Invalid

description.p: This field specifies CRC seed operation mode.

field-enum-def.field-enum-desc: CRC seed is incremental per logic block.
CRC seed is constant over all blocks

description.desc-title: PI1 Application Tag Check Bit Mask
description.p: This field contains application tag check bit mask. When a bit in the bit mask is set to 0, the corresponding bit in application tag will be checked if application tag check is enabled. When a bit in the bit mask set to 1, the corresponding application tag will not be checked even if application tag check is enabled.
This field contains PI1 input block size in bytes for PI1 engine. The input block size is defined for the input data stream into PI1 engine.
The input block is Dword aligned. The lower 2 bits should be set always to 0.
This field specifies the offset in bytes from start of the input data stream for PI1 engine.
The data offset is Dword aligned. The lower 2 bits should be set always to 0.
This field contains16-bit CRC (in PI Guard field) seed when PI1PIMode = 0 (NVMe). It is lower 16-bit of the CRC seed when PI1PIMode = 1 (Extended) or PI1PIMode = 2 (CRC64).
This field contains16-bit Application Tag when PI1PIMode = 0 (NVMe). It is high 16-bit of the CRC seed when PI1PIMode = 1 (Extended), or middle (bit 31:16) PI1PIMode = 2 (CRC64).
This field contains 32-bit Initial Reference Tag when PI1PIMode = 0 (NVMe) or PI1PIMode = 1 (Extended), or high 32-bit of the CRC seed when PI1PIMode = 2 (CRC64).
This field contains the lower 32-bits of the 40-bit starting address of source memory region 0.
The memory region is Dword aligned. The lower 2 bits of this field should be set always to 0.
This field contains the upper 8-bit of the 40-bit starting address of source memory region 0.
When this bit is set to one, this is the last memory region associated with the transfer. No more subsequent source memory region address exists in this message.
This field contains the number of bytes associated with source memory region 0.
The memory region is Dword aligned. The lower 2 bits of this field should be set always to 0.
This field contains the lower 32-bits of the 40-bit starting address of destination memory region 0.
The memory region is Dword aligned. The lower 2 bits of this field should be set always to 0.
This field contains the upper 8-bit of the 40-bit starting address of destination memory region 0.
When this bit is set to one, the bytes specified by this memory region are discarded and are not written to controller memory.
When this bit is set to one, this is the last memory region associated with the transfer. No subsequent destination memory region address exists in this message.
This field contains the number of bytes associated with destination memory region 0.
The memory region is Dword aligned. The lower 2 bits of this field should be set always to 0.
This field contains the lower 32-bits of the 40-bit starting address of source memory region 1.
The memory region is Dword aligned. The lower 2 bits of this field should be set always to 0.
This field contains the upper 8-bit of the 40-bit starting address of source memory region 1.
When this bit is set to one, this is the last memory region associated with the transfer. No more subsequent source memory region address exists in this message.
This field contains the number of bytes associated with source memory region 1.
The memory region is Dword aligned. The lower 2 bits of this field should be set always to 0.
This field contains the lower 32-bits of the 40-bit starting address of destination memory region 1.
The memory region is Dword aligned. The lower 2 bits of this field should be set always to 0.
This field contains the upper 8-bit of the 40-bit starting address of destination memory region 1.
When this bit is set to one, the bytes specified by this memory region are discarded and are not written to controller memory.
When this bit is set to one, this is the last memory region associated with the transfer. No subsequent destination memory region address exists in this message.
This field contains the number of bytes associated with destination memory region 1.
The memory region is Dword aligned. The lower 2 bits of this field should be set always to 0.
